EXERCISE 18 on page 300:

This is a C++ program that exercises the circular-shift
function shift().  Although the function shift() itself
is straighforward, the function main() uses some advanced
ideas.

In main(), we use the function shift() to circular-shift
successive groups of 5 characters on each input line.  After
shifting and writing as many groups of 5 as we can, we write
out the remaining characters on the line, if any.  When we
do this on a readable file, the results, although visually
interesting, are not very readable.

As a test of our program, we will circular-shift this READ_ME
message five times.

